UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1665
1 A RESOLUTION adjourning the Senate in honor and loving memory of Tatum
2 Elizabeth Dale.
3 WHEREAS, Tatum Elizabeth Dale was born in Murray, Kentucky, on May 10,
4 1990, to Bill and Ellen Dale; and
5 WHEREAS, Tatum Elizabeth Dale was a proud graduate of Calloway County High
6 School and the University of Kentucky; and
7 WHEREAS, after graduating college, Tatum Elizabeth Dale volunteered to work on
8 Congressman Andy Barr's first congressional campaign and continued to work for him
9 for the next 15 years, where she would go on to hold almost every position in the Barr
10 congressional office including: Scheduler, Field Representative, Deputy District Director,
11 District Director, and most recently, Deputy Chief of Staff and Campaign Manager; and
12 WHEREAS, Tatum Elizabeth Dale was an extraordinary young woman with a
13 servant's heart and the capacity to love and make people feel special. She had the ability
14 to connect with people and get to know them in a way that was genuine and from the
15 heart; and
16 WHEREAS, Tatum Elizabeth Dale was a devout servant of the Lord, and a member
17 of the Calvary Baptist Church in Lexington, Kentucky, where she found a passion for
18 mission work. She also chaperoned countless Honor Flights carrying veterans to
19 Washington D.C.; and
20 WHEREAS, Tatum Elizabeth Dale had an endearing love for her family. She
21 understood the blessing of family and showed her love constantly in big and small ways;
22 and
23 WHEREAS, Tatum Elizabeth Dale passed away on December 24, 2025, at the
24 University of Kentucky Medical Center in Lexington, Kentucky. She was preceded in
25 death by her grandparents, J.C. "Billy" and Cora Elizabeth "Libby" Mahan and Rev. B.G.
26 and Doris Dale, and her uncle, Joe "Skip" Ginn; and
27 WHEREAS, Tatum Elizabeth Dale is survived by her parents, Bill and Ellen Dale;
Page 1 of 2
